@node 37.6 "37.6"
Public release in E, compiled with Amiga E 2.1b

    o Made code public domain and released to Aminet and Fidonet
    o Removed brag line and keyfile dependency
    o Changed code to compile under vanilla Amiga E 2.1b compiler
@endnode

@node 37.5 "37.5ß"
Internal release in E, compiled with Amiga E 2.1b, EHS 1.00 and EPP 1.1

    o StripTag integrated into AmigaETag
    o NOSTRIP switch created
    o Improved Spot tag file compatibility
    o Brag lines are now placed on the same line as the last line of the
      tag, if possible
    o Added BRAGNL argument
    o Created AmigaGuide documentation
    o Minor optimizations
@endnode

@node 37.4 "37.4ß"
Internal release in E, compiled with Amiga E 2.1b

    o Trashed prefix bug fixed
    o Missing keyfile bug fixed
    o Fixed potential alpha and beta keyfile conflict
    o Minor internal code enhancements
@endnode

@node 37.3 "37.3ß"
Internal release in E, compiled with Amiga E 2.1b

    o Switched to final form of brag line
    o Added the ADDNL switch for appending an additional newline to the end
      of taglines
    o Changed default keyfile location to PROGDIR:
@endnode

@node 37.2 "37.2ß"
Internal release in E, compiled with Amiga E 2.1b

    o Fixed an offset bug when appending a tagline to the end of a file
    o Added keyfile registration
    o Added the COUNT keyword for counting the number of taglines available
    o Fixed a bug causing badly-corrupted keyfiles to crash the program
    o Corrected a spelling error in the program template
    o Slightly reduced executable size
    o Included two supplementary programs, Convert and StripTag
    o Made brag line more compact
@endnode

@node 37.1 "37.1ß"
Internal release in E, compiled with Amiga E 2.1b

    o Integrated functionality of RexxTag and RexxTagII into a single
      program
    o Removed ARexx-dependent program restrictions
    o Changed argument handling to be Style Guide compliant
    o Drastically improved internal error-checking
    o Greatly improved the speed of searches and output by using buffered
      AmigaDOS I/O functions
    o Made filename arguments generic
    o Use of indexed tag files no longer requires editing the tag file,
      instead, a command line argument is used
    o Added support for user-defined tagline prefixes
    o Created new argument for specifying the seed used for random number
      generation
    o Allowed the selection of a specific tagline to be used instead of a
      randomly-generated one
    o Multi-line tagline support added
    o User-definable line break string argument created
    o Created option to output to default console
    o Added support for possible future inclusion of keyfile for registered
      users of a shareware release
    o Minor internal optimizations
@endnode

